gov.usgs.anss.fetcher

Class BalerWfdiscDirectory

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.fetcher.BalerWfdiscDirectory

  • public class BalerWfdiscDirectory
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates a directory obtained from a baler 44. This normally is of the files in the wfdisc area which are used to access data files in the data and cont areas. This is curled in one piece and the HTML returned is about 130 kB. This means a slow link Q330/Baler44 might be blocked off significantly during this operation. It reads the HTML of the directory from /WDIR/wfdisc directory which is just a list of files of the form NN-SSSS_4-YYYYMMDDHHMMSS.wfdisc.gz. All files cause a Wfdisc object to be created in the dirs variable. Other classes will use this list of wfdisc files.

    This work was partially funded by Cal Tech under a contract in 2016.

        public BalerWfdiscDirectory(java.lang.String host,

                            java.lang.String path,
                            int limitRate,
                            int timeout,
                            Baler44Request parent)
                     throws java.io.IOException
        This checks to see if the station last wfdisc.dir is late enough to cover this ending time, if it is, the cached one is parsed, if not then the URL is read. This is used for Compressed balers
        Parameters:
        host - of the form of an IP address or DNS host
        port - The port to use
        station - The name of the station like USDUG
        directoryName - The name of the directory containing wfdisc files (e.g. "wfdisc or wfdisk-20151210220550")
        end - The ending time that needs to be covered
        path - Path where baler related scratch and cache files are to be kept
        limitRate - Limit of the data rate in bits per second
        timeout - The timeout in seconds to abort at
        parent - A logging EdgeThread
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if one occurs getting the data using curl or if reading the resulting filename is bad
